This script turns every second page of a PDF document. It acts as a wrapper for the "pdftk shuffle" command

turnEverySecondPage <filename> <parity>
where <parity> is either string: "even" or "odd"

DEPENDENCIES: pdftk(->java), pdfinfo
TRIVIAL DEPENDENCIES: awk, grep, echo

It talks to you like a butler
MIT license, use freely

for the interested reader:
Did thou made acquainance with a person that deliberately scanned every second page of a document the wrong way round? Thy suffering shall end O end user! May turnEverySecondPage turn every second page of thy pdf. By it's delicate splitting, turning and merging abilities it splits, turns and merges thy PDF like nothing else. Thou shalt not suffer any more !
